messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Explanation:
- The seed() method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/seed", method = RequestMethod.POST). There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix, so the full path is exactly "/admin/seed".
- The method attribute explicitly restricts the handler to POST only. Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not on framework runtime behaviours like automatic OPTIONS/HEAD responses), only POST is accepted and all other HTTP methods are not.
